1. PERSONAL & NON-COMMERCIAL USE
   Free use for individuals, education, research, and personal projects.

2. SMALL COMPANY EXEMPTION
   Companies are exempt from the charity payment if they meet ALL:
   - Fewer than 10 employees
   - Annual gross revenue under $1.5 million USD (or equivalent)
   - Not a subsidiary of a larger entity
   OR if their gross revenue is at least 40% below the average revenue
   for their market sector (as defined by standard industry classifications)

3. COMMERCIAL USE BY LARGER COMPANIES
   Any company exceeding the above thresholds that uses this Software
   commercially must:
   a) Pay 1.5% of gross revenue attributable to this Software (or 1.5%
      of total gross revenue if not separately measurable) to a charity
      selected by public vote of the user community
   b) Contribute any modifications, improvements, or bug fixes made
      to this Software back to the original project via pull request
      within 90 days of deployment

   Payment must be made annually, within 90 days of fiscal year end,
   with public disclosure of the amount paid and charity selected.

4. ATTRIBUTION
   All users of this Software must retain the original copyright notice,
   this license, and a link to the source repository in all copies or
   substantial portions of the Software. Commercial users must also
   include attribution in their product's documentation, credits, or
   "About" screen.

5. PATENT GRANT
   Each contributor grants you a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free patent
